Foreign Companies

It is the policy of the government of Ivory Coast to contribute to the growth of the cocoa farming industry. Foreign companies and local have been involved in this initiative. The conditions for this agreement can also be revised or changed on the basis of improving conditions for farmers or a significant change in the economy.

The latest agreement which announced a minimum national producer price was revised on the September 6, 2012. The market is highly dynamic dealing with buyers from across the world which boost making quotes and prices complicated.

This also makes having connections important when buying and selling cocoa beans. A contract is very important as trust is often required to ensure producers get paid on the basis of quality.
